  <name>gtkrypt</name>
  <summary>Encrypt and decrypt files securely</summary>
  <description>
    <p>gtkrypt is a GNOME application for encrypting and decrypting files using AES-256-GCM with Argon2id key derivation. It provides a simple drag-and-drop interface for file encryption and a personal vault for organizing sensitive files, records, and notes.</p>
    <p>Features include:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Encrypt and decrypt files with strong AES-256-GCM encryption</li>
      <li>Personal data vault with file, record, and note support</li>
      <li>Optional keyfile-based two-factor encryption</li>
      <li>Drag-and-drop file handling</li>
      <li>Batch encryption and decryption</li>
      <li>Modern GNOME/Libadwaita interface</li>
    </ul>
  </description>
  <launchable type="desktop-id">io.github.gtkrypt.desktop</launchable>
  <url type="homepage">https://github.com/codedsleep/gtkrypt</url>
  <url type="bugtracker">https://github.com/codedsleep/gtkrypt/issues</url>
